<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/72158896-body-peace-university"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1507091773i/72158896._UY100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/72158896-body-peace-university">Body Peace University</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Read this book multiple times. Where things bother you, it is good to ask yourself if you have bought into that myth or use it to survive in some way.<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Read this book multiple times. Where things bother you, it is good to ask yourself if you have bought into that myth or use it to survive in some way. Sometimes the statements that are unsettling most challenge our views. Not saying her information is correct or that her research in that area is perfect. just wondering if you fixate on that potential detail to avoid uncomfortable information.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
